        <initializer>	Z_KERNEL_STACK_DEFINE_IN(sym, size, __kstackmem); \
	<ref refid="group__thread__stack__api_1ga16eed4de8bbcf2132f0947844c3874b8" kindref="member">K_THREAD_HW_SHADOW_STACK_DEFINE</ref>(sym, \
					K_THREAD_HW_SHADOW_STACK_SIZE(size))</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Define a toplevel kernel stack memory region in pinned section. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>See <ref refid="group__thread__stack__api_1ga9e05e3cb5aa5b72d6f19e2f327313271" kindref="member">K_KERNEL_STACK_DEFINE()</ref> for more information and constraints.</para>
